Hello?

08:51.781 --> 08:53.700
I hate to interrupt
your day, honey,

08:53.700 --> 08:55.910
<i>but I need your help
with these pies.</i>

08:55.910 --> 08:58.705
<i>I'm so tired, I'm starting
to see the weirdest things.</i>

08:58.705 --> 09:00.707
Weird? Yes!
I'll be right home!

09:01.791 --> 09:04.085
Urn, that was
partially my fault.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.837
(YAWNS)

09:05.837 --> 09:08.214
The pies aren't the only
things that are burnt!

09:08.214 --> 09:10.800
Kalakamaka!

09:10.800 --> 09:13.219
Laka ullafallabalaka!

09:13.219 --> 09:16.097
I gotta get
out of here.

09:16.097 --> 09:18.349
Oh. That didn't go over
as well as I'd hoped.

09:18.349 --> 09:21.811
Hmm, perhaps I need
to spruce it up more!

09:21.811 --> 09:24.063
Spruce! Spr...

09:24.063 --> 09:25.231
Cw!

09:25.231 --> 09:28.610
I do believe
I've sprained my elbow.

09:28.610 --> 09:30.862
Maybe some fresh air
will help wake me...

09:30.862 --> 09:32.113
(SCREAMS)

09:32.113 --> 09:33.364
Hi, Morn
Phineas?

09:35.950 --> 09:37.452
Okay, found it!

09:37.452 --> 09:39.829
Okay, I just have to take
three steps back.

09:39.829 --> 09:41.122
One, two...

09:41.122 --> 09:45.126
Ow! Why do I keep
stacking buckets?

09:45.126 --> 09:46.753
Curse you,
Perry the Platypus!

09:51.758 --> 09:53.259
(SNIGGERS)

09:53.259 --> 09:54.385
This is gonna be epic!

09:54.385 --> 09:56.888
Okay, Morn! Here I am!

09:56.888 --> 09:58.890
Candace, do you see
what I'm seeing?

10:01.643 --> 10:04.646
I don't see anything.

10:04.646 --> 10:07.273
That's it!
I'm lying down.

10:07.273 --> 10:09.901
(SCREAMING)

10:09.901 --> 10:11.778
I can see everything
so well now!

10:11.778 --> 10:14.280
Yes, whoever invented those
gizmos inside that machine

10:14.280 --> 10:17.659
must be a person who's dedicated
his or her life to good.

10:17.659 --> 10:19.160
Oh, man!

10:19.160 --> 10:21.663
Ignore the upside-down man,
Balthazar.

10:21.663 --> 10:23.373
<i>MAN:</i> (OVER <i>PA) Ladies and
gentlemen, our keynote speaker</i>

10:23.373 --> 10:27.669
<i>on the history of the Ornithorhynchon
tribe, Lawrence Fletcher.</i>

10:27.669 --> 10:28.920
Thank you for
coming here today

10:28.920 --> 10:30.296
to hear my speech
on the history

10:30.296 --> 10:32.006
of the ancient
Ornithorhynchan tribe.

10:32.006 --> 10:34.425
The Ornithorhynchans were a
platypus-worshipping society.

10:34.425 --> 10:36.427
Why is his arm in a sling?

10:36.427 --> 10:38.763
That's what bothers you
about this?

10:42.809 --> 10:44.811
That nap did me
a world of good!

10:44.811 --> 10:46.688
I feel so much better now.

10:47.897 --> 10:50.692
Mmm, no, maybe not.
Back to bed.

